# SECTION 4 — Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Mermaid Flowchart — End-to-End Algorithm Pipeline

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    startA([Start]) --> input1[/Read Plaintext String/]
    input1 --> clean[Convert to Uppercase and Remove Non-Letters]
    clean --> pad{Pad with X if Length is Odd}
    pad --> map[Map Each Letter to Number 0 to 25]
    map --> blockForm[Group Numbers into Blocks of Size n]
    blockForm --> keyVal[Validate Key: gcd of det K and 26 must equal 1]
    keyVal --> invComp[Compute K inverse mod 26 using Extended Euclidean]
    invComp --> menu{User Chooses Encrypt or Decrypt}
    menu -- Encrypt --> mulEnc[Multiply Key K by Plaintext Block mod 26]
    menu -- Decrypt --> mulDec[Multiply K inverse by Ciphertext Block mod 26]
    mulEnc --> numMap1[Map Numbers 0 to 25 back to Letters A to Z]
    mulDec --> numMap1
    numMap1 --> concat[Concatenate Blocks into Final String]
    concat --> out[/Display Result/]
    out --> stopA([Stop])
```

## 4.2 Mermaid Block Diagram — Java Program Module Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph IO[User Interface Layer]
        ui1[Main Method with Menu Loop]
    end

    subgraph LOGIC[Cryptographic Logic Layer]
        enc[encrypt Method]
        dec[decrypt Method]
    end

    subgraph MATH[Linear Algebra Helpers]
        mulM[multiply 2x2 Matrices mod 26]
        mulV[multiply Matrix by Vector mod 26]
        modInv[modInverse via Extended Euclidean]
        invK[inverse2x2 of Key Matrix]
        modN[mod26 Normaliser]
    end

    ui1 -- read text and choice --> enc
    ui1 -- read ciphertext --> dec
    enc --> mulV
    enc --> modN
    dec --> invK
    dec --> mulV
    dec --> modN
    invK --> modInv
    invK --> mulM
    invK --> modN
    mulM --> modN
    mulV --> modN
```

## 4.3 Mermaid Data-Flow Diagram — Encryption Block Transformation

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    ptxt[Plaintext String HELP] --> enc1[Map H to 7, E to 4, L to 11, P to 15]
    enc1 --> blk[Form Blocks P1 equals 7,4 and P2 equals 11,15]
    blk --> mul1[K times P1 mod 26 equals 3,11]
    blk --> mul2[K times P2 mod 26 equals 11,4]
    mul1 --> ch1[Cipher Block 1 equals D L]
    mul2 --> ch2[Cipher Block 2 equals L E]
    ch1 --> join[Concatenate]
    ch2 --> join
    join --> ctxt[Final Ciphertext D L L E]
```

## 4.4 Mermaid Sequence Diagram — Decryption Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant M as Main Loop
    participant D as decrypt Method
    participant I as inverse2x2
    participant V as multiplyVec
    participant N as mod26

    U->>M: Choose option 2 and enter DLLE
    M->>D: decrypt DLLE, K
    D->>I: compute K inverse mod 26
    I->>N: normalise all entries
    I-->>D: return Kinv
    loop For each 2 letter block
        D->>V: multiplyVec Kinv, C block
        V->>N: wrap each sum in mod 26
        V-->>D: return numeric plaintext block
    end
    D-->>M: return HELP
    M-->>U: print HELP
```

