### Question A — 14 Marks **[KTU University Exam — May 2024 Model]**

**(a) [7 marks]** Given the key matrix $\mathbf{K} = \begin{bmatrix} 3 & 2 \\ 5 & 7 \end{bmatrix}$ and the plaintext `"HELP"`, perform Hill Cipher encryption. Show every modular reduction step clearly.

**(b) [7 marks]** Write the **complete Java program** to implement both encryption and decryption of the Hill Cipher using the same key. Include helper methods for modular inverse and matrix multiplication.

#### Model Solution

**Part (a) — Encryption (7 marks):**

**Step 1 — Encode plaintext:** `"HELP"` → $[7, 4, 11, 15]$ (using $A=0$). (0.5 mark)

**Step 2 — Form blocks of size $n=2$:** $\mathbf{P}_1 = \begin{bmatrix} 7 \\ 4 \end{bmatrix}$, $\mathbf{P}_2 = \begin{bmatrix} 11 \\ 15 \end{bmatrix}$. (0.5 mark)

**Step 3 — Validate the key:** $\det(\mathbf{K}) = (3)(7) - (2)(5) = 11$. $\gcd(11, 26) = 1$ ✓ (key valid). (0.5 mark)

**Step 4 — Block 1 encryption:** (2 marks)

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{C}_1 &= \begin{bmatrix} 3 & 2 \\ 5 & 7 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} 7 \\ 4 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 29 \\ 63 \end{bmatrix} \equiv \begin{bmatrix} 3 \\ 11 \end{bmatrix} \pmod{26}
\end{aligned}
$$

→ Ciphertext block 1 = `"DL"`.

**Step 5 — Block 2 encryption:** (2 marks)

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{C}_2 &= \begin{bmatrix} 3 & 2 \\ 5 & 7 \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} 11 \\ 15 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 63 \\ 160 \end{bmatrix} \equiv \begin{bmatrix} 11 \\ 4 \end{bmatrix} \pmod{26}
\end{aligned}
$$

→ Ciphertext block 2 = `"LE"`.

**Step 6 — Final ciphertext:** `"HELP"` → `"DLLE"`. (0.5 mark)

**Step 7 — Self-verification using the inverse** (optional, for full marks): compute $\mathbf{K}^{-1} = \begin{bmatrix} 3 & 14 \\ 9 & 5 \end{bmatrix}$ and apply it to "DLLE" to recover "HELP". (1 mark)

