- ☐ Hill Cipher is a **polygraphic substitution cipher** based on **linear algebra modulo 26**.
- ☐ Encryption: $\mathbf{C} = \mathbf{K} \cdot \mathbf{P} \pmod{26}$ — Decryption: $\mathbf{P} = \mathbf{K}^{-1} \cdot \mathbf{C} \pmod{26}$.
- ☐ Letter encoding: **A=0, B=1, …, Z=25** (always uppercase, strip non-letters).
